The paper proposes a novel approach for imputing missing values in multivariate, geo-tagged time series data using the self-attention mechanism. This involves processing each dimension sequentially while maintaining order-independence. This work involves machine learning and data mining techniques, which are typically covered in the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.DB (Databases).
